[We are very grateful to Bob Swanepoel for these details. The [06 posting
had been cleared by Drs. Klaucke & Martin, who we are sure did not intend
to convey an impression of confusion. It was evident that livestock were
dying from multiple causes, and that RVF and anthrax were both still
possible etiologies for the human disease as of 1 Jan.1998.
Last week we had a full & detailed description of the laboratory studies on
human specimens but were asked not to post them without clearance from
Nairobi. Here at ProMED-mail one of our priorities, after providing
information on emerging disease outbreaks, is to help, not hinder, those in
the field. We submitted some 15+ case reports to Steve Berger, who ran them
through his diagnostic program GIDEON and declared them to be RVF. The
result was shared with Nairobi.
Not infrequently we are party to information that we cannot post for a
variety of serious reasons, including the personal safety of informants.
ProMED-mail is being under-utilised by the contributing members if we are
prevented from passing on information. - Mods. MHJ, JW
